{
  "text": "Increasing the protein content in the fish feed usually results in increased fish growth rate (Bibiano-Melo et al. Bar with no superscript in common differ significantly (p<0.05). Data are mean ± standard error (2000) and [CITATION_1] . [CITATION_2] used five different diets containing 40, 45, 50, 55 and 60% crude protein to culture murray cod, Maccullochella peelii peelii and observed the highest SGR in fish fed with 50% crude protein containing diet. [CITATION_3] used almost similar diets to culture snakehead, Channa striata and observed the highest SGR in fish fed with 55% crude protein containing diet.",
